| HistoryText             = The realm of Asgard existed in an endless cycle of death and rebirth. Those Who Sit Above in Shadow lived off the energy released by [[Ragnarok (Event)|Ragnarök]], and caused the cycle to continue.{{r|Thor Vol 2 #81|85}}

They were allegedly the creators of the [[Asgardians]], but were possibly created by them instead, as myths which became reality.{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard #17}}

Those Who Sit Above in Shadow were first seen when Loki tried to win their favor. [[Loki Laufeyson (Earth-616)|Loki]] attempted good deeds, but they were not pleased by his actions and rejected him.{{r|X-Men/Alpha Flight #1|2}}

When [[Odin Borson (Earth-616)|Odin]] sent [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]] to Earth to learn a lesson in humility by becoming human, a loophole was created in the cycle, as Those Who Sit Above in Shadow could no longer predict what Thor would do when influenced by man, and thus could not keep Thor bound by his strand of fate. This was part of Odin's plan. When the final Ragnarok arrived Thor hung himself on Yggdrasil to gain vast wisdom and runic magic, and learned who was behind the cycle. Thor destroyed the Loom of the Fates, and broke the thread that holds the destiny of [[Asgardians]], from which Those Who Sit Above in Shadow were absorbing energy. With their source of energy destroyed and the cycle broken, Those Who Sit Above in Shadow seemingly perished along with the rest of the Asgardian worlds and people.{{r|Thor Vol 2 #84|85}}

Those Who Sit Above in Shadow revealed themselves to still be alive a few hours before the universe collapsed due to the Multiversal phenomena known as the [[Glossary:Incursion|incursions]]. They appeared before Odin in his dreams, announcing the upcoming end of all there was.{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard #14}}

When all of reality was eventually destroyed, the trickster [[Loki Laufeyson (Ikol) (Earth-616)|Loki]] was one of the few survivors of the universe, having used magic to both exit reality and safely contain the essence of his fellow Asgardians.{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard Vol 1 16}} After finding himself in a blank void of nothingness, Loki was confronted by Those Who Sit Above in Shadows, who demanded to be given the Asgardians' essence to feed on it. Loki defied Those Who Sit Above in Shadow, and even put into question their origin and existence. If the gods such as the Asgardians come from the stories that have been told about them, it was possible that the gods of the gods didn't create the gods, but had been created by them. Unable to answer or even counter the questions posed by Loki, Those Who Sit Above in Shadows fled.{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard #17}}

