| Notes                   = * Those Who Sit Above In Shadow possess a scale of power well beyond the level of Asgardians. They have demonstrated the ability to manipulate great power, feeding off energy given by the Ragnarok cycle. They once teleported Loki to [[Svartalfheim]] when he fell out of their favor. Yet they could not predict Thor destroying the Loom of the Fates, so their claim of omniscience is hyperbole.{{r|Thor Vol 2 85}}
* It was hypothesized by [[Loki Laufeyson (Ikol) (Earth-616)|Loki]] that Those Who Sit Above In Shadow could have been created by the [[Asgardians]]' beliefs, or were even [[Beyonders]].{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard #17}}
** To be noted that their sentences "Slay your enemies and all you desire shall be yours" and "Nothing you dream of is impossible for us to accomplish"{{r|Loki: Agent of Asgard #14}} mimicked the [[Beyonder (Earth-616)|Beyonder]]'s.{{r|Marvel Super Heroes Secret Wars #1}}
* They were also stated to share certain similarities with the [[Primal Gods]].{{r|All-New Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe A to Z #11|; Those Who Sit Above in Shadow's entry}}
* It was recently revealed that Thor would go to the Elder-Sleep where he could commune with the spirits and the old dead kings whenever he used [[Mjolnir]] to switch places with [[Donald Blake (Earth-616)|Donald Blake]]. When Thor most recently traded places with Blake, the elder spirits and the ancient kings who turned their eyes from him looked like three of Those Who Sit Above In Shadow.{{r|Thor Vol 6 9}}
| Trivia                  = * [[Stan Lee|Stan Lee]] (jokingly) stated that their names were Larry, Larry, Larry, Ralph and Larry.<ref>[http://brevoortformspring.tumblr.com/post/139069925913/those-who-sit-above-in-shadow-do-you-have-any Stan Lee's post on Brevoort Tumblr]</ref>
